# Laravel + AI (PHP)

## Layout

- **`app/Agents`:** One primary concern per agent class; register tools explicitly; keep prompts and behavior testable.
- **`app/Tools`:** Laravel AI tools (function calling) — small surface area, clear input/output types, no hidden I/O.
- **`app/Services/AI`:** Resolution engine steps (retrieval, ranking, response assembly, guardrails). Prefer composing agents/tools from here rather than bloating controllers or models.

## Data + vectors

- Use **Eloquent** models with **pgvector** columns where the schema uses vectors.
- Prefer **`similaritySearch`** (or the project’s established vector query API) for nearest-neighbor retrieval; avoid duplicating the same raw SQL in multiple services.

```php
// BAD — scattered raw vector SQL across controllers
// DB::select('... <-> ? ...', [$embedding]);

// GOOD — centralized model/repository method using Eloquent vector support
// $matches = Article::query()->similaritySearch('embedding', $embedding)->limit(10)->get();
```

(Adjust model/table names to match the codebase.)

## PHP style

- **`declare(strict_types=1);`** on new PHP files where the project already does so.
- Prefer **constructor injection**, **DTOs/value objects** for tool inputs/outputs when complexity grows.
- Controllers stay thin: validate, authorize, delegate to services/agents.
